race.comment: The Melbourne Cup-winning stable look to have found the perfect race for CAVITY BAY (1), who was held up rounding the bend at Bendigo and wasn't beaten far at Caulfield last Saturday. Like the back-up into a 2000m race for the mare who ran 5th in the SA Derby earlier this year. WINSTON (5) turned in a sound effort last time but found one better at Caulfield Heath over 1800m, beaten 1.5 lengths. Should be at his peak now. Will appreciate a drop in grade. URBAN OUTLOOK (2) didn't get warm first up off a lengthy spell, but ran an improved race last start and will relish getting to 2000m. BURLINGTON GATE (7) is yet to fill a placing in two runs since resuming from a spell, the latest when eighth over 1856m at Kyneton, but is ready for this trip and ran well in much stronger races last prep.
